I was there twice, and it seemed really hard to flag down someone to take our order or request for additional cutlery etc. And I don't understand restaurants that don't invest in big plates for the main courses. Isn't it easier to eat noodles off of a big plate? Anyway, great food though.
Of the Asian options in the area this is one of the better ones. Large menu and fast service.
Very tasty pho ga (chicken). They had fast service and fresh ingredients.
The crazy noodles were delicious!
Adequate Vietnamese food in a deteriorating restaurant. The carpet is almost ready to crawl out on its own, and should probably be encouraged to do so.
